{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c8904d7c-4511-40bf-b37e-c46c280d20f7","content":"Two things changed with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Filter syntax** — MTP uses a *tree-node filter* (path-based), not VSTest filter expressions. The test tree is `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<method>`, with `[Key=Value]` for traits.\n\n**2. Translation of your filter:**\n\n| Old (VSTest) | New (MTP tree-node filter) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` |\n| `&` (AND) | combine in one expression |\n\nYour new command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n- `/**/` — matches any assembly/namespace prefix  \n- `*IntegrationTests*` — matches the class node (contains)  \n- `/**` — matches any method under it  \n- `[Category=Smoke]` — filters on the `Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")`\n\nIf running the built executable directly instead of `dotnet test`, use the `--treenode-filter` flag:\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3601d879-71ed-4e74-815a-c6121dec85c6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). The key changes are:\n\n1. **Filter syntax changes with MTP**: When using `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, the `--filter` option from VSTest is replaced by MTP's `--filter` which uses a different syntax (Tree Node Filter / TRX filter expression).\n\n2. **The old filter**: `\"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"` uses VSTest filter syntax where:\n   - `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` means FQN contains \"IntegrationTests\"\n   - `&` means AND\n   - `Category=Smoke` matches the Trait\n\n3. **MTP filter syntax**: MTP uses a completely different filter expression language based on tree node paths with property filters. Instead of the VSTest synta